- `"executionRoleArn"`: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the task execution role that
  grants the Amazon ECS container agent permission to make Amazon Web Services API calls on
  your behalf. The task execution role is required for daemon tasks that pull container
  images from Amazon ECR or send container logs to CloudWatch.

- `"memory"`: The amount of memory (in MiB) used by the daemon task. It can be expressed as
