timeout, after which the `SIGKILL` value is sent and the containers are forcibly stopped.
This signal can be defined in your container image with the `STOPSIGNAL` instruction and
will default to `SIGTERM`. If the container handles the `SIGTERM` value gracefully and exits
within 30 seconds from receiving it, no `SIGKILL` value is sent.

